<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0127 </DOCNO><TEXT>The conference took place in 5 sessions: 1. radiation monitoring of dischargesand of the environment of nuclear power plants, 2. monitoring and evaluationof the radiation situation in nuclear power plants, 3. equipment formonitoring nuclear power plants and their surrounding areas, 4. mathematicalmodelling and evaluation of the radiation impact of the nuclear planton the environment, 5. evaluation of sources and transport of radioactivematerials in nuclear power plants and minimization of the environmentalimpacts of nuclear power plants. The aim of the conference was to exchangeknowledge and experience in providing radiation safety in Czechoslovaknuclear power plants. (E.S.).</TEXT></DOC>